                         API Server connects using
                     apiserver-etcd-client.crt (from etcd CA)

ğŸ”· Explanation of the Map (Simple Terms)
1. The Root CA

Main cluster Certificate Authority.

Signs certificates for API server, controller manager, scheduler, kubelet.

2. API Server Certificates

apiserver.crt: secure HTTPS endpoint

apiserver-kubelet-client.crt: talks to kubelets

apiserver-etcd-client.crt: talks to etcd

API server is the heart â€” everything passes through it.

3. Kubelet Certificates

Each worker node has its own certificate signed by root CA.

Workers request their cert via CSR â†’ approved automatically.

4. Front Proxy Certificates

Used by aggregated APIs like metrics-server, dashboards, webhooks.

5. etcd Certificates

They have their own CA, separate from Kubernetes CA.

etcd uses:

server.crt

peer.crt

healthcheck-client.crt

apiserver-etcd-client.crt (signed by etcd CA)

All etcd nodes must mutually trust each other.
